briefdescription.para: If true steeringCurve and steeringMaxAngleCurve will be applied to the wheel steering. If false the curves will not be applied and the values set via advanced tweakable sliders are applied instead.
This curve defines the rate of wheel turn related to the speed of the wheel. The x values of the curve are the speed and the y values are the rate of wheel turn.

This curve defines the maximum steering angle of wheel as a multiplier that will be applied based on the speed of the wheel. The x values of the curve is the speed and the y values are the multiplier. y values are clamped between 0 and 1.
This is how fast the wheel will turn/respond to player input.
Method fires once the module has been added to the part. Use for first time setup. Module will not have loaded fully by this point
Use OnLoad to load any additional data from the ConfigNode provided
Use OnSave to serialize additional module information into the ConfigNode provided
